The paper deals with motion prediction of surrounding vehicles for autonomous vehicles, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of LSTM models for prediction involves machine learning (cs.CV, cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with uncertainty and complex scenarios, which are relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
